er socio-political impact of disciplinary psychology in Western liberal democracies.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aAutonomy (Psychology). 0aPsychology. 4aPsychology : Developmental Psychology. 7aPSYCHOLOGY / General.2bisacsh1 aSugarman, Jeff, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aThompson, Janice, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013z978311148737340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780791486849?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780791486849423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780791486849/original  a978-3-11-148737-3  SUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles